<br>
This is naturally part of the game.  Unfortunately, a warriors downtime is usually because of a casters downtime.  <br>
<br>
Anyway, I was pondering various ways in which warriors(and other tanks) can super infuse themselves with hps so that healing is drastically cut down.<br>
<br>
Regen spells are the most basic way.  But regen adds so little.  Well, I've got this crazy idea of a super combo of regen effects that can heal for incredible amounts.<br>
<br>
Regrowth(Shaman spell) + 2 healing bard songs + Regen armor(Fungus tunic etc)  + Mark of Karn(cleric spell).<br>
<br>
Can anyone even tell me how much healing this would provide? (per tick for example).  The first 3 would be passive healing while the 4th would be in terms of actively hitting a mob.  I've seen this in LIMITED form.  A monk friend of mine had Regrowth + tunic + Mark of Karn.  During a fight she went from 3 bubbles of health to full health in a matter of seconds.  It -looked- like she'd been healed, but it was all just a combination of the healing effects!<br>
<br>
If anyone can give a rough estimate of how much hps this heals this would be awesome.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    <br>
<br>
-Aileen of Quellious<br>
 56 Myrmidon of Shadows of The Unseen<br>
<br>
<br>
