 <p></p><i>Edited by <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uaileenovarr.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aileen OVarr</A> at: 9/7/00 5:03:02 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/unorok.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Norok</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ironcross.org/images/ironcross.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <b>knows that Warriors are Superior</b><br>   <font color=#FF0000>(9/7/00 10:01:48 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Healing Super Combo.  Has anyone tried this?</span><hr size=1> Well this is the info that I think is correct.<br>
<br>
Regrowth(Shaman spell)= 15 <br>
2 healing bard songs  = no Clue<br>
Fungus tunic          = 15<br>
Mark of Karn          = 0<br>
Normal Regen          = 4 (Troll and Iksar are 6 or 7 I belivee)<br>
<br>
Mark of Karn is a Damage Shield that when cast is cast on the enemy. It is like a DOT sorta...<br>
It heals you 10 points per HIT but you have to be hitting the creature to get any benifit of the spell its self.<br>
<br>
Even though I love my Oggok Cleaver and will never part with it - when Our Cleric Breaks out the Mark of Karn I switch to my two fasted 1 handed weapons. I know I will do less damage but I tuant better and I hit alot more therefore healing myself alot more then I would otherwise.<br>
<br>
So with just Regrowth (expensive spell to cast 300 mana I believe) and Fungal Tunic you can heal 34 points a tick. Add bard songs and I have no clue - I honestly do not know how many HP a bard can heal. However I do believe Bards would be MUCH better served grouped with the Casters spinning the Mana song so your down time is even less.<br>
<br>
Just my 2 coppers<br>
<br>
 <p><b>Da Rok</b><br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=glachummcslachum>Glachum McSlachum</A></span><br> <b>knows that Warriors are Superior</b><br>   <font color=#FF0000>(9/7/00 4:44:08 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Healing Super Combo.  Has anyone tried this?</span><hr size=1> Have one o' those flame throwers summon up some bandages or buy some yeself.  50% is better than nothing.  If your in the middle of a fight?  Sorry, no other suggestions than what ye already said. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ukorrellian.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Korrellian</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <b>knows that Warriors are Superior</b><br>   <font color=#FF0000>(9/8/00 6:05:20 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Healing Super Combo.  Has anyone tried this?</span><hr size=1> The other day in Karnors our Bard indicated his songs gave 11 points a tick.  I wear a Rubi BP, had the Bard singing away with a Shaman regen on, and found that I rarely dipped below 1 bub of health.  When I did, I simply sat a minute after the fight and would super heal.  Little or no heal spells required, but it was difficult convincing the Bard to stay on the regen and not switch to the mana song hehe. <p>Korrellian Kullraven<BR>Warchief, Sabretooth Bear Clan<BR>Your freinds from the North Lands</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/umeddik.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Meddik</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <b>knows that Warriors are Superior</b><br>   <font color=#FF0000>(9/8/00 7:32:39 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/wahooker/Meddikicon.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Healing Super Combo.  Has anyone tried this?</span><hr size=1> This is a great setup when damage is being spread evenly among multiple melee classes, Especially if you have a melee heavy party.<br>
<br>
If all damage is focused on a single warrior, Complete Heal may be more effecient, I'm not really sure. <p><CENTER><B>Meddik Sawbones</B><BR><A HREF="http://24.19.82.195/~orbis/">Orbis Honesti</A> Guild, Bristlebane Server</CENTER>
